他们是这么说的
That's what they're saying.

43
00:03:01,481 --> 00:03:04,177
我要他所有的资料
I want everything they've got on him.

44
00:03:39,852 --> 00:03:41,513
他们在哪里？
Where are they?

45
00:03:42,956 --> 00:03:44,821
那是什么声音？
What the hell is that?

46
00:03:51,297 --> 00:03:52,992
我们走
Let's go.

47
00:03:57,303 --> 00:03:59,396
-我们要跑到另一边才行 -什么？
- We gotta make it to the other side! - What?

48
00:03:59,572 --> 00:04:01,096
-跑到铁轨另一边 -你疯了
- Make it to the other side! - Crazy!

49
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:07,774
-快点 -快跑
- Come on! - Come on, run!

50
00:04:11,718 --> 00:04:15,779
快跑，动作快
We gotta go! Run! Let's go! Move it, move it!

51
00:04:17,290 --> 00:04:19,520
-快点 -火车速度加快了
- Go! - The thing is gaining speed, man!

52
00:04:22,862 --> 00:04:24,762
-火车太快了！ -穿过去！
- It's going too fast! - Go through!

53
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:27,161
-什么？ -穿过去
- What? - Go through!

54
00:04:29,435 --> 00:04:31,027
麦可
Michael!

55
00:04:32,472 --> 00:04:33,734
不要开枪
Hold your fire!

56
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:47,117
站住 我会开枪的，史柯菲
Freeze! I will gun you down, scofield!

57
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:51,946
麦可，快来
Michael, come on.

58
00:05:05,772 --> 00:05:09,469
-直升机在哪里？ -他们回地上加油
- Where's the aerial unit? - They're back on the ground refueling.

59
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:12,372
该死的家伙
Son of a bitch.

60
00:05:37,570 --> 00:05:41,370
片名：越狱风云

61
00:05:44,043 --> 00:05:46,170
剧名：全力缉捕

62
00:05:48,247 --> 00:05:51,705
先生，媒体准备好了
Sir, the media is ready.

63
00:06:21,514 --> 00:06:26,508
可以的话，我想稍微谈谈 约翰魏克斯布思
I'd like to talk about John Wilkes Booth for a moment, if I could.

64
00:06:26,686 --> 00:06:28,654
谋杀林克总统的人
Abraham Lincoln's killer.

65
00:06:28,821 --> 00:06:30,413
12天
Twelve days.

66
00:06:30,590 --> 00:06:32,751
花了这么久才找到他
That's how long it took to find him.

67
00:06:32,925 --> 00:06:36,452
他当时在日记中写下 阴影是他的朋友K
In his journal during this period, he wrote that the shadow was his friend...

68
00:06:36,629 --> 00:06:38,290
夜晚是他的世界
...the night his domain.

69
00:06:39,866 --> 00:06:42,232
他承认了，那股驱使罪犯K
He acknowledged that neuroses driving the criminal,,,

70
00:06:42,402 --> 00:06:45,030
犯罪的原动力K
,,, to commit the original crime is compounded,,,

71
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:48,734
会因逃亡而加大
,,, magnified by flight,

72
00:06:49,275 --> 00:06:52,267
是因为紧追在后 警犬的声响
By the sounds of dogs at his heels,

73
00:06:52,779 --> 00:06:54,269
恐惧变成妄想症
Fear becomes paranoia.

74
00:06:55,281 --> 00:06:57,340
妄想最后变成精神病
Paranoia, ultimately psychosis,

75
00:06:59,152 --> 00:07:02,610
我提到这件事是因为 140年后
I bring this up because in 140 years...

76
00:07:02,789 --> 00:07:06,657
逃犯的基本心态仍未改变
...the fundamental mind of the escaped man has not changed.

77
00:07:06,826 --> 00:07:11,490
逃犯一样是人，一样会害怕
The escaped man is still human, he is still afraid...

78
00:07:11,664 --> 00:07:14,963
一样会不顾一切企图逃亡
...and he will stop at nothing in his attempted flight.

79
00:07:16,402 --> 00:07:17,926
不过我们很幸运
Fortunately for us,,,

80
00:07:18,104 --> 00:07:24,009
我们的对手只有影子和夜晚相助
,,, while our quarry has shadow and night as his ally,,,

81
00:07:24,177 --> 00:07:26,805
而我们有更得力的助手
...we have something far greater.

82
00:07:28,014 --> 00:07:29,879
就是电视
Television.

83
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:33,013
我期望国内所有在看电视的人
I would encourage everyone who is watching...

84
00:07:33,486 --> 00:07:36,887
请仔细看看这些面孔
...everyone in this country, to take a good look at these faces.

85
00:07:37,423 --> 00:07:41,792
这八人是现在美国的头号通缉犯
These men right here are now the eight most wanted men in America.

86
00:07:48,901 --> 00:07:52,564
我以为计划周详 你看到有多少人在追我们吗？
I thought I thought this out. You saw all those guys back there?

87
00:07:52,738 --> 00:07:54,968
重点是他们在后面，我们在上面
The key is they're back there and we're up here.

88
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:56,836
这样能维持多久？
Yeah. And how long is that gonna last?

89
00:07:57,009 --> 00:07:59,204
对，尤其我们现在一毛钱也没有
Especially since we don't have a pot to piss in...

90
00:07:59,378 --> 00:08:01,573
都要感谢亚布兹神奇消失的飞机
...thanks to Abruzzi's magically disappearing jet.

91
00:08:01,747 --> 00:08:03,738
反正你也上不了飞机
You were never gonna be on that plane.

92
00:08:03,916 --> 00:08:05,907
别以为我不知道你打算去哪
Don't think I don't know where you were going.

93
00:08:06,085 --> 00:08:08,246
-我要去哪里？ -喔，我不知道
- Where am I going? - Oh, I don't know.

94
00:08:08,421 --> 00:08:09,888
犹他州？
Utah?

95
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:12,981
你打算何时才告诉我们钱的事？
You planning on telling us about the money?

96
00:08:13,359 --> 00:08:14,690
什么钱？
What money?

97
00:08:15,294 --> 00:08:19,025
五百万美金 威莫兰埋在犹他州沙漠的钱
Five million dollars that Westmoreland planted in the desert in Utah.

98
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:24,500
-你根本不知道你在说什么 -是你希望我不知道
- You don't know what you're talking about. - You wish I didn't know.

99
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:26,194
等等，什么钱？
Wait, wait. What money?

100
00:08:29,275 --> 00:08:30,503
典狱长
Warden.

101
00:08:31,677 --> 00:08:34,840
FBI现在介入太早了，不是吗？
It's a little early for the FBI to be showing up, don't you think?

102
00:08:35,114 --> 00:08:37,275
我明白，调查还是由你主导
Look, I get it. It's still your investigation.

103
00:08:37,450 --> 00:08:40,544
但是只要逃犯越过州界 就是联邦事务了
Once those criminals cross state lines, it'll become a federal matter.

104
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:43,689
-不会发生这种事的 -希望你是对的
- Yeah, well, that is not gonna happen. - I hope you're right.

105
00:08:43,856 --> 00:08:47,553
所以我建议你 先撇开任何政治成见
That's why I suggest that we cut through any interagency politics from the outset.

106
00:08:47,727 --> 00:08:50,560
-一切坦白透明化 -那当然
- Full transparency. - Absolutely.

107
00:08:50,730 --> 00:08:52,197
很好
Good.

108
00:08:52,365 --> 00:08:55,129
那么或许可以跟我谈谈 丹奎迪医生
Then maybe you can tell me about Dr. Tancredi.

109
00:08:55,701 --> 00:08:57,692
没什么好谈的
There's nothing to tell.

110
00:08:57,870 --> 00:09:01,067
我听说她有可能帮助逃犯逃亡
From what I'm hearing, she may have abetted the escapees.

111
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:03,731
她打开门让他们逃出去
Opened the door that allowed them to get out.

112
00:09:04,043 --> 00:09:07,706
-我说过，没什么好谈的 -你不太坦白，典狱长
- Like I said, there's nothing to tell. - You're not being very transparent, warden.

113
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:11,646
-听着，我不谈下属的事 -也许你应该谈
- Look, I don't discuss my staff. - Maybe you should...

114
00:09:11,817 --> 00:09:14,081
因为她可能是整件事的关键
...because she may be the key to this thing.

115
00:09:15,154 --> 00:09:17,622
我们需要找她谈谈
We need to speak with her.

116
00:09:18,624 --> 00:09:23,220
曼宏先生，就现在而言 她不会跟任何人谈的
Well, right now, Mr. Mahone, she's not gonna be speaking with anyone.

117
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:31,964
情况如何？
How we doing?

118
00:09:32,138 --> 00:09:34,402
点滴提供她水分
Well, the IVs are hydrating her.

119
00:09:34,574 --> 00:09:38,271
每半小时替她注射 半毫克Q酸那克酸
We've got her on naloxone infusion. Half-milligram per hour.

120
00:09:38,444 --> 00:09:40,776
你认为苏醒的机会有多大？
What do you think the chances are?

121
00:09:40,947 --> 00:09:44,007
我们尽力了 一切得靠她自己
Well, we've done everything on our end. It's really up to her.

122
00:09:44,183 --> 00:09:49,052
她坚持就能活命，放弃就会死
Either she fights and lives, or she quits and dies.

123
00:10:39,905 --> 00:10:41,873
你在做什么K
Hey, what do you think...?

124
00:10:46,512 --> 00:10:48,503
你想做什么随便你
Do whatever thing you've gotta do, man.

125
00:10:53,552 --> 00:10:57,249
对了，小子K
Oh, and boy...

126
00:10:58,491 --> 00:11:01,255
要是你敢报警，我手上的东西K
If you call the cops, I will put this thing right here...

127
00:11:02,828 --> 00:11:04,728
就会插进你的眼睛
...in your eye.

128
00:11:09,101 --> 00:11:10,932
谢谢
Thank you.

129
00:11:28,187 --> 00:11:30,246
他是结构工程师？
Structural engineer, huh?

130
00:11:30,423 --> 00:11:33,017
这种人很少会有这么多刺青在身上
Not the kind you'd expect to get that much ink.

131
00:11:33,192 --> 00:11:34,420
应该说不可能刺青
Not the kind at all.

132
00:11:35,461 --> 00:11:38,692
你觉得这种刺青 要多久才能完成？
How long do you think it'd take to get something like that done?

133
00:11:38,864 --> 00:11:41,298
一百小时，两百小时
A hundred hours. Two hundred.

134
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:45,062
帮他刺青的师傅 一定和他相处了不少时间
Tattoo artist who gave it to him must've spent a lot of time with him, then.

135
00:11:46,172 --> 00:11:47,833
我去查是谁
I'll find out who it was.

136
00:11:51,544 --> 00:11:53,273
-贝里克先生 -不要烦我
- Mr. Bellick. - Don't talk to me.

137
00:11:53,446 --> 00:11:55,812
好，但这样会很难合作
Fine. But it's gonna make collaboration kind of hard.

138
00:11:55,981 --> 00:11:58,814
合作？ 我的手下在外身处危险之中
Collaboration? I got men out here in harm's way...

139
00:11:58,984 --> 00:12:00,815
你却在开记者会
...and you're giving press conferences.

140
00:12:00,986 --> 00:12:02,419
媒体是工具
The press is a tool.

141
00:12:02,588 --> 00:12:05,113
媒体抓到他们的速度 比猎犬还要快
It'll bring those men back quicker than bloodhounds will.

142
00:12:05,291 --> 00:12:06,519
我们不需要你
We don't need you.

143
00:12:06,692 --> 00:12:09,718
我们已掌握他们的行踪 抓到他们是迟早的事
We're hot on the trail, it's a matter of time till we nail them.

144
00:12:09,895 --> 00:12:12,125
我不满意你只是掌握行踪
The problem I find with being on a trail...

145
00:12:12,298 --> 00:12:15,495
因为这代表你永远慢猎物一步
...is that, by definition, you'll always be behind your prey.

146
00:12:17,803 --> 00:12:19,737
我们走着瞧
We'll see about that.

147
00:12:23,142 --> 00:12:25,576
（蒙大拿州，布拉克富特）

148
00:12:27,113 --> 00:12:28,512
我手上没有武器
I'm not armed.

149
00:12:28,681 --> 00:12:31,775
请见谅 我现在很难信任他人
You'll have to excuse me if I'm a little short on trust at the moment.

150
00:12:31,951 --> 00:12:35,751
我向你保证，小姐 我绝对不会伤害你
I assure you, young woman, I'm the furthest thing from a threat.

151
00:12:35,921 --> 00:12:38,515
我确定我吃了止痛药 全身无力
I think the Percocet pretty much ensures that.

152
00:12:38,691 --> 00:12:43,253
很好，那么你应该不介意 我拍下证据给子孙欣赏
Good. Then you won't mind if I capture this moment for posterity.

153
00:12:43,429 --> 00:12:45,488
你拍照也没用的
Won't do you any good.

154
00:12:45,865 --> 00:12:48,959
某人因为谋杀你的罪名要被处死 你都毫不在乎吗？
You don't care that somebody's gonna be executed for your murder?

155
00:12:49,135 --> 00:12:51,933
选择林克柏劳栽赃的人 不是我
I'm not the one who chose Lincoln Burrows as the fall guy.

156
00:12:52,104 --> 00:12:53,571
那是谁？
Who did?

157
00:12:53,739 --> 00:12:55,104
你姐姐，总统？
Your sister, the president?

158
00:12:55,274 --> 00:12:57,868
你不懂，我是这整件事的囚犯
You don't understand. I'm a prisoner to all of this.

159
00:12:58,043 --> 00:13:00,170
算了吧，你大可以出面说清楚
Oh, come on. You could've come forward.

160
00:13:00,346 --> 00:13:03,076
在开始前 你就可以阻止整件事
You could've stopped this thing before it even got started.

161
00:13:03,249 --> 00:13:05,547
不，我真的是囚犯
No, I really am a prisoner.

162
00:13:05,718 --> 00:13:07,242
现在你也成了囚犯
And now you are too.

163
00:13:08,821 --> 00:13:11,346
从你把门关上那一刻开始
The moment you let the door shut behind you.

164
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:22,123
外面没有保全人员K
Didn't it strike you as curious...

165
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:24,235
你不觉得怪吗？
...that there wasn't any security out there?

166
00:13:24,403 --> 00:13:26,963
门只能从外面打开
The doors only open from the outside.

167
00:13:27,139 --> 00:13:30,506
玻璃是两寸厚的防弹玻璃
The glass is 2 inches thick, bulletproof.

168
00:13:32,845 --> 00:13:35,211
你逃不出去了，小姐
